Description.Text: This is a very grand hotel which is rich in history. (0109AB)

Located in a quiet area of Whitehall overlooking the Thames, a short walk from the Houses of Parliament, Big Ben, Westminster Abbey, St James Park, Buckingham Palace, Trafalgar Square and The National Gallery.

These rooms are larger and more luxurious than the standard rooms. All the rooms are furnished very elegantly in a traditional style, offering modern facilities. The rooms and bathrooms are in excellent condition.
It is a traditional and impressive sandstone building.

The restaurant is located on the ground floor. Leading on from the lobby is a traditional lounge, where afternoon tea is served, leading on from the lounge is the bar, and to the left the very traditional restaurant with the atmosphere of a gentlemen's club, being furnished with heavy furniture. Due to its proximity to Parliament it is frequented by many ministers.
The large lobby is laid out with marble and features a small seating area in front of an open fire with a lounge area decorated in pastel colours and comfortable sofas.
